## Edge Case Solutions Summary

| Edge Case | How Recalculate Fixes It |
|-----------|-------------------------|
| **Direction bug** | Sort by `end_date` → the earlier-ending order always gets priority. Works regardless of creation order |
| **Date changes** | Recalculate called after date update → re-evaluates all pairs from scratch |
| **Expected return stale** | `updateOrder()` updates `expected_return_date` on cleaning records before calling recalculate (requires `UpdateCleaningRecordDTO` fix) |
| **Multiple priority** | Recalculate checks ALL orders, not just one pair → won't miss Order B when Order C is cancelled |
| **Item changes** | Recalculate called for both old and new products → old products lose stale priority, new products gain correct priority |
| **Cancellation** | Delete cancelled order's records → recalculate → remaining orders re-evaluated correctly |
| **Deletion** | Fetch affected products before delete → delete cleaning records → delete order → recalculate for each product |

